{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["49-EPH-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"EPH"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Ephesians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Paul’s Letter to the Ephesians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Ephesians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Eph \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Paul’s Letter to the Ephesians \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"EPH 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 1:1"},"Paul, an apostle of Masih Isa through the will of Allah, to the saints who are at Ephesus, and the faithful in Masih Isa:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 1:2"},"Grace to you and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 1:3"},"Blessed be Allah and Father of our Lord Al Masih Isa, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly\nplaces in Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 1:4"},"even as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world, that we would be holy and without defect before him in\nlove, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 1:5"},"having predestined us for adoption as children through Al Masih Isa to himself, according to the good pleasure of his\ndesire, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 1:6"},"to the praise of the glory of his grace, by which he freely gave us favour in the Beloved,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 1:7"},"in whom we have our redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of our trespasses, according to the riches of his grace,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 1:8"},"which he made to abound towards us in all wisdom and prudence,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 1:9"},"making known to us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he purposed in him\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 1:10"},"to an administration of the fullness of the times, to sum up all things in Masih, the things in the heavens and the\nthings on the earth, in him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 1:11"},"We were also assigned an inheritance in him, having been foreordained according to the purpose of him who does all things\nafter the counsel of his will, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 1:12"},"to the end that we should be to the praise of his glory, we who had before hoped in Masih.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 1:13"},"In him you also, having heard the word of the truth, the Good News of your salvation—in whom, having also believed, you\nwere sealed with the promised Holy Spirit, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 1:14"},"who is a pledge of our inheritance, to the redemption of Allah’s own possession, to the praise of his glory.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 1:15"},"For this cause I also, having heard of the faith in the Lord Isa which is amongst you, and the love which you have\ntowards all the saints, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 1:16"},"don’t cease to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 1:17"},"that Allah of our Lord Al Masih Isa, the Father of glory, may give to you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the\nknowledge of him, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 1:18"},"having the eyes of your hearts",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “understanding” instead of\n“hearts”"]}],"caller":"+"}," enlightened, that you may know what is the hope of his calling, and what are the riches of the glory of his\ninheritance in the saints, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 1:19"},"and what is the exceeding greatness of his power towards us who believe, according to that working of the strength of his\nmight \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 1:20"},"which he worked in Masih, when he raised him from the dead and made him to sit at his right hand in the heavenly places,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 1:21"},"far above all rule, authority, power, dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this age, but also in that\nwhich is to come. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EPH 1:22"},"He put all things in subjection under his feet, and gave him to be head over all things for the assembly,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EPH 1:23"},"which is his body, the fullness of him who fills all in all.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"EPH 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 2:1"},"You were made alive when you were dead in transgressions and sins,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 2:2"},"in which you once walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the\nspirit who now works in the children of disobedience. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 2:3"},"We also all once lived amongst them in the lusts of our flesh, doing the desires of the flesh and of the mind, and were by\nnature children of wrath, even as the rest. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 2:4"},"But Allah, being rich in mercy, for his great love with which he loved us,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 2:5"},"even when we were dead through our trespasses, made us alive together with Masih—by grace you have been saved—\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 2:6"},"and raised us up with him, and made us to sit with him in the heavenly places in Masih Isa,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 2:7"},"that in the ages to come he might show the exceeding riches of his grace in kindness towards us in Masih Isa;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 2:8"},"for by grace you have been saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; it is the gift of Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 2:9"},"not of works, that no one would boast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 2:10"},"For we are his workmanship, created in Masih Isa for good works, which Allah prepared before that we would walk in them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 2:11"},"Therefore remember that once you, the Gentiles in the flesh, who are called “uncircumcision” by that which is called\n“circumcision” (in the flesh, made by hands), \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 2:12"},"that you were at that time separate from Masih, alienated from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the\ncovenants of the promise, having no hope and without Allah in the world.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 2:13"},"But now in Masih Isa you who once were far off are made near in the blood of Masih.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 2:14"},"For he is our peace, who made both one, and broke down the middle wall of separation,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 2:15"},"having abolished in his flesh the hostility, the law of commandments contained in ordinances, that he might create in\nhimself one new man of the two, making peace, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 2:16"},"and might reconcile them both in one body to Allah through the cross, having killed the hostility through it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 2:17"},"He came and preached peace to you who were far off and to those who were near.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 2:18"},"For through him we both have our access in one Spirit to the Father.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 2:19"},"So then you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but you are fellow citizens with the saints and of the household of\nAllah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 2:20"},"being built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Masih Isa himself being the chief cornerstone;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 2:21"},"in whom the whole building, fitted together, grows into a holy temple in the Lord;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EPH 2:22"},"in whom you also are built together for a habitation of Allah in the Spirit.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"EPH 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 3:1"},"For this cause I, Paul, am the prisoner of Masih Isa on behalf of you Gentiles,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 3:2"},"if it is so that you have heard of the administration of that grace of Allah which was given me towards you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 3:3"},"how that by revelation the mystery was made known to me, as I wrote before in few words,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 3:4"},"by which, when you read, you can perceive my understanding in the mystery of Masih,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 3:5"},"which in other generations was not made known to the children of men, as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and\nprophets in the Spirit, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 3:6"},"that the Gentiles are fellow heirs and fellow members of the body, and fellow partakers of his promise in Masih Isa\nthrough the Good News, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 3:7"},"of which I was made a servant according to the gift of that grace of Allah which was given me according to the working of\nhis power. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 3:8"},"To me, the very least of all saints, was this grace given, to preach to the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Masih,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 3:9"},"and to make all men see what is the administration",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:9\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “fellowship” instead of “administration”"]}],"caller":"+"}," of the mystery which for ages has been hidden in Allah, who created\nall things through Al Masih Isa, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 3:10"},"to the intent that now through the assembly the manifold wisdom of Allah might be made known to the principalities and\nthe powers in the heavenly places, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 3:11"},"according to the eternal purpose which he accomplished in Masih Isa our Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 3:12"},"In him we have boldness and access in confidence through our faith in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 3:13"},"Therefore I ask that you may not lose heart at my troubles for you, which are your glory.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 3:14"},"For this cause, I bow my knees to the Father of our Lord Al Masih Isa,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 3:15"},"from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 3:16"},"that he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, that you may be strengthened with power through his Spirit\nin the inner person, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 3:17"},"that Masih may dwell in your hearts through faith, to the end that you, being rooted and grounded in love,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 3:18"},"may be strengthened to comprehend with all the saints what is the width and length and height and depth,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 3:19"},"and to know Masih’s love which surpasses knowledge, that you may be filled with all the fullness of Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 3:20"},"Now to him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in\nus, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 3:21"},"to him be the glory in the assembly and in Masih Isa to all generations forever and ever. Amen.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"EPH 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 4:1"},"I therefore, the prisoner in the Lord, beg you to walk worthily of the calling with which you were called,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 4:2"},"with all lowliness and humility, with patience, bearing with one another in love,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 4:3"},"being eager to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 4:4"},"There is one body and one Spirit, even as you also were called in one hope of your calling,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 4:5"},"one Lord, one faith, one baptism, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 4:6"},"one Allah and Father of all, who is over all and through all, and in us all.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 4:7"},"But to each one of us, the grace was given according to the measure of the gift of Masih.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 4:8"},"Therefore he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“When he ascended on high, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he led captivity captive, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gave gifts to people.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 68:18"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 4:9"},"Now this, “He ascended”, what is it but that he also first descended into the lower parts of the earth?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 4:10"},"He who descended is the one who also ascended far above all the heavens, that he might fill all things.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 4:11"},"He gave some to be apostles; and some, prophets; and some, evangelists; and some,\nshepherds",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, pastors"]}],"caller":"+"}," and teachers; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 4:12"},"for the perfecting of the saints, to the work of serving, to the building up of the body of Masih,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 4:13"},"until we all attain to the unity of the faith and of the knowledge of the Son of Allah, to a full grown man, to the\nmeasure of the stature of the fullness of Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 4:14"},"that we may no longer be children, tossed back and forth and carried about with every wind of doctrine, by the trickery\nof men, in craftiness, after the wiles of error; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 4:15"},"but speaking truth in love, we may grow up in all things into him who is the head, Masih,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 4:16"},"from whom all the body, being fitted and knit together through that which every joint supplies, according to the working\nin measure of each individual part, makes the body increase to the building up of itself in love.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 4:17"},"This I say therefore, and testify in the Lord, that you no longer walk as the rest of the Gentiles also walk, in the\nfutility of their mind, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 4:18"},"being darkened in their understanding, alienated from the life of Allah because of the ignorance that is in them, because\nof the hardening of their hearts. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 4:19"},"They, having become callous, gave themselves up to lust, to work all uncleanness with greediness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 4:20"},"But you didn’t learn Masih that way, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 4:21"},"if indeed you heard him, and were taught in him, even as truth is in Isa:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EPH 4:22"},"that you put away, as concerning your former way of life, the old man that grows corrupt after the lusts of deceit,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EPH 4:23"},"and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EPH 4:24"},"and put on the new man, who in the likeness of Allah has been created in righteousness and holiness of truth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EPH 4:25"},"Therefore putting away falsehood, speak truth each one with his neighbour. For we are members of one another.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EPH 4:26"},"“Be angry, and don’t sin.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 4:4"]}],"caller":"+"}," Don’t let the sun go down on your wrath,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EPH 4:27"},"and don’t give place",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, opportunity"]}],"caller":"+"}," to the Iblis.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EPH 4:28"},"Let him who stole steal no more; but rather let him labour, producing with his hands something that is good, that he may\nhave something to give to him who has need. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EPH 4:29"},"Let no corrupt speech proceed out of your mouth, but only what is good for building others up as the need may be, that it\nmay give grace to those who hear. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EPH 4:30"},"Don’t grieve the Holy Spirit of Allah, in whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EPH 4:31"},"Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, outcry, and slander be put away from you, with all malice.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EPH 4:32"},"And be kind to one another, tender hearted, forgiving each other, just as Allah also in Masih forgave you.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"EPH 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 5:1"},"Be therefore imitators of Allah, as beloved children. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 5:2"},"Walk in love, even as Masih also loved us and gave himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice to Allah for a\nsweet-smelling fragrance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 5:3"},"But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not even be mentioned amongst you, as becomes saints;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 5:4"},"nor filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not appropriate, but rather giving of thanks.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 5:5"},"Know this for sure, that no sexually immoral person, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, has any\ninheritance in the Kingdom of Masih and Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 5:6"},"Let no one deceive you with empty words. For because of these things, the wrath of Allah comes on the children of\ndisobedience. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 5:7"},"Therefore don’t be partakers with them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 5:8"},"For you were once darkness, but are now light in the Lord. Walk as children of light,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 5:9"},"for the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 5:10"},"proving what is well pleasing to the Lord. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 5:11"},"Have no fellowship with the unfruitful deeds of darkness, but rather even reprove them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 5:12"},"For it is a shame even to speak of the things which are done by them in secret.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 5:13"},"But all things, when they are reproved, are revealed by the light, for everything that reveals is light.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 5:14"},"Therefore he says, “Awake, you who sleep, and arise from the dead, and Masih will shine on you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 5:15"},"Therefore watch carefully how you walk, not as unwise, but as wise,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 5:16"},"redeeming the time, because the days are evil. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 5:17"},"Therefore don’t be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 5:18"},"Don’t be drunken with wine, in which is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 5:19"},"speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 5:20"},"giving thanks always concerning all things in the name of our Lord Al Masih Isa, to Allah, even the Father;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 5:21"},"subjecting yourselves to one another in the fear of Masih.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EPH 5:22"},"Wives, be subject to your own husbands, as to the Lord. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EPH 5:23"},"For the husband is the head of the wife, as Masih also is the head of the assembly, being himself the saviour of the\nbody. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EPH 5:24"},"But as the assembly is subject to Masih, so let the wives also be to their own husbands in everything.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EPH 5:25"},"Husbands, love your wives, even as Masih also loved the assembly, and gave himself up for it;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EPH 5:26"},"that he might sanctify it, having cleansed it by the washing of water with the word,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EPH 5:27"},"that he might present the assembly to himself gloriously, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing; but that it\nshould be holy and without defect. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EPH 5:28"},"Even so husbands also ought to love their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves his own wife loves himself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EPH 5:29"},"For no man ever hated his own flesh; but nourishes and cherishes it, even as the Lord also does the assembly;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EPH 5:30"},"because we are members of his body, of his flesh and bones.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EPH 5:31"},"“For this cause a man will leave his father and mother, and will be joined to his wife. The two will become one\nflesh.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["5:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 2:24"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EPH 5:32"},"This mystery is great, but I speak concerning Masih and of the assembly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EPH 5:33"},"Nevertheless each of you must also love his own wife even as himself; and let the wife see that she respects her husband.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"EPH 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EPH 6:1"},"Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EPH 6:2"},"“Honour your father and mother,” which is the first commandment with a promise:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EPH 6:3"},"“that it may be well with you, and you may live long on the earth.”\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 5:16"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EPH 6:4"},"You fathers, don’t provoke your children to wrath, but nurture them in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EPH 6:5"},"Servants, be obedient to those who according to the flesh are your masters, with fear and trembling, in singleness of your\nheart, as to Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EPH 6:6"},"not in the way of service only when eyes are on you, as men pleasers, but as servants of Masih, doing the will of Allah\nfrom the heart, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EPH 6:7"},"with good will doing service as to the Lord, and not to men,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EPH 6:8"},"knowing that whatever good thing each one does, he will receive the same good again from the Lord, whether he is bound or\nfree. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EPH 6:9"},"You masters, do the same things to them, and give up threatening, knowing that he who is both their Master and yours is in\nheaven, and there is no partiality with him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EPH 6:10"},"Finally, be strong in the Lord, and in the strength of his might.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EPH 6:11"},"Put on the whole armour of Allah, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the Iblis.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EPH 6:12"},"For our wrestling is not against flesh and blood, but against the principalities, against the powers, against the world’s\nrulers of the darkness of this age, and against the spiritual forces of wickedness in the heavenly places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EPH 6:13"},"Therefore put on the whole armour of Allah, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to\nstand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EPH 6:14"},"Stand therefore, having the utility belt of truth buckled around your waist, and having put on the breastplate of\nrighteousness, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EPH 6:15"},"and having fitted your feet with the preparation of the Good News of peace,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EPH 6:16"},"above all, taking up the shield of faith, with which you will be able to quench all the fiery darts of the evil one.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EPH 6:17"},"And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the\nword",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["from the Greek “ῥῆμα” (rhema), which means “spoken\nword”"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Allah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EPH 6:18"},"with all prayer and requests, praying at all times in the Spirit, and being watchful to this end in all perseverance and\nrequests for all the saints: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EPH 6:19"},"on my behalf, that utterance may be given to me in opening my mouth, to make known with boldness the mystery of the Good\nNews, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EPH 6:20"},"for which I am an ambassador in chains; that in it I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EPH 6:21"},"But that you also may know my affairs, how I am doing, Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful servant in the Lord,\nwill make known to you all things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EPH 6:22"},"I have sent him to you for this very purpose, that you may know our state and that he may comfort your hearts.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EPH 6:23"},"Peace be to the brothers, and love with faith, from Allah the Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EPH 6:24"},"Grace be with all those who love our Lord Al Masih Isa with incorruptible love. Amen.\n"]}]}